      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum linear elastic model with frictional contact justified for the loading regime; sensitivity analysis performed on friction coefficient and material modulus.",
      "rationale": "Pedicle screw construct under quasi-static ASTM F1717 loading is well within the linear elastic regime for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V). Frictional contact (mu=0.2) at screw-rod interface justified by published tribology data. Sensitivity analysis shows QoI variation < 3% over mu range 0.15–0.30. Model form level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of production Ti-6Al-4V lot; geometric inputs from CMM measurement of test specimens.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa) and yield strength (880 MPa) from tensile coupon tests on production bar stock (n=5, CV < 2%). Screw and rod geometry from CMM reports (tolerance ±0.01 mm). UHMWPE block modulus from supplier datasheet confirmed by compression test. All inputs traceable to measurement records. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N ≥ 10 constructs from production lots assembled per device IFU; CMM verification of each specimen geometry prior to testing.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-representative components. CMM reports for each specimen confirm geometry within drawing tolerances. Constructs assembled by trained technician per IFU SP-ASSY-F1717-001. Sample adequacy confirmed at level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of anticipated clinical loading; at minimum two load magnitudes or fixture offsets evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single ASTM F1717 standard offset (100 mm) and single load rate (25 mm/min). Only one test condition evaluated, limiting coverage of the clinical loading envelope. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3; this shortfall is documented as an accepted limitation given the prescriptive nature of the ASTM standard and the availability of corroborating literature data."
